This season Mark Sloan and Lexie Die. The doctors involved in the plane crash pool their funds with the Harper Avery foundation (175M) and buy the hospital. They form a board of directors that is headed by relatively new doctor Jackson Avery.

Storylines:
Meredith discovers she is pregnant and has a baby boy. During the delivery she has to guide the new interns how to stop and repair her spleen. Eventually Bailey saves the day and the new baby is called Bailey.

Bailey marries Ben and Ben continues to live and intern in California. Also, Bailey has staph infection and kills 3 patients.

Karev is being difficult as usual and is in love with Joe Wilson; an intern who grew up in her car and foster care.

Arizona Robbins is upset that Torres ordered the removal of her leg and starts dating the new HOT doctor in town.

Torres is focused solely on having _______________ with Robbins and finding bones to grow and manipulate.

Derrick's hand is messed up and he can't perform surgery. THIS IS A REPEAT of the Preston Burke storyline. Eventually Derrick's hand is healed and he can perform surgeries again.

Brookes is Derrick's new favorite intern even though she is quirky odd and weird.

Jackson is having _____________ with the new intern STEPHANIE. Stephanie and Jackson have NO chemistry.

April falls in love with Matt, the medic, and he asks her to marry him. She says YES but is in love with Jackson.

Matt is a male medic who is a virgin.

The best storyline is when YANG went to Minnesota. She took a special interest in an older surgeon and he gave her the advice to be herself and don't let anyone make her feel like she has to be mediocre to fit in. After the surgeon dies, YANG returns to Seattle and resumes relations with Owen. She discovers that she is not enough for OWEN; he needs a child.

Owen decides to adopt a boy, but the boy's father awakes from his comma. Owen is trying to convince himself that his life will be okay without children.

This season was better than the last 4 seasons and the interns are better too. The attendings are now too old for this mess. It is time to make new stars for the show.

Especilaly annoying is Meredith's fat face and skinny body. Also, her lack of enthusiasm for acting is obvious. I wish we all could be paid MILLIONS to do a job we really don't have a strong interest in doing.

From the TV SHOW the PRACTICE: Rebecca makes an appearance as Meredith's OB.

The DVD's themselves are wonderful and I would recommend this series to anyone.

However, the packaging on these is not great. All five discs are in the one case. This would normally not be a problem, except that the case is made very cheaply and could break in shipping. As long as you are prepared for that though, this is the best you can really find. Just be aware that the case might arrived cracked.
